               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18310407-287-person1974">
                  THOMAS 
                  HOBBS KING
               <interp inst="t18310407-287-person1974" type="surname" value="HOBBS KING"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310407-287-person1974" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310407-287-person1974" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a Police-officer. On the night of the 29th of March I stopped the prisoner in Maiden-lane, Islington, at half-past nine o'clock - I saw her before I stopped her, in company with a young man, who had this bundle under his arm; he gave it to the prisoner, and they separated - she came on, and he staid in the road; they had not seen me or Harris, who was with me - the prisoner then came on, and as soon as she got sight of me, she dropped the bundle; the young man ran across the fields - this is the bundle, it contains the articles stated; they were wet when I took them.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18310407-287-person1975">
                  ALFRED 
                  HARRIS
               <interp inst="t18310407-287-person1975" type="surname" value="HARRIS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310407-287-person1975" type="given" value="ALFRED"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310407-287-person1975" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a Police-constable. I was with King, and took up the bundle - the prisoner said she knew nothing of it, and that she was one hundred yards from it, but she was not more than five yards from it - she said she knew nothing of the young man; but the next morning she said she was in company with him, and had some conversation with him about some money for some shoes - he goes by the name of Daddy Lee - that was the name she expressed.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18310407-287-person1976">
                  JAMES 
                  PECKETT
               <interp inst="t18310407-287-person1976" type="surname" value="PECKETT"></interp>
